#1 A 59-year-old gentleman with no family history of colon cancer, now with a recently-diagnosed sigmoid colon malignancy
The biopsies have been reviewed and reveal an adenocarcinoma.
I think it will be very important for us to determine exactly where this is located, to make certain this is in the sigmoid colon, and not in the proximal rectum.  The CT-scan also suggested his right adrenal gland was enlarged, we will confirm this by a repeat CT-scan of the adrenal gland.  Depending on these results, I will see the patient in return with Colorectal Surgical consultation.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at CDSC.

